08/12/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- At least 18 people were killed and 12 injured when a truck collided with a bus Thursday (December 7th), sending both vehicles plunging from a bridge into a river. The crash occurred in the town of Byala, some 320km northeast of Sofia. The tragedy prompted Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev to cut short his visit to Portugal. (24 Chasa, Trud, Sega - 08/12/06; bTV, Mediapool, News.bg - 07/12/06)
